{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, Event cameras also perform better in low illumination and overexposure due to their higher dynamic range.Because of the aforementioned features and advantages, research on vision tasks centered around event cameras is gradually emerging [23].",
    "A series of benchmark datasets are proposed for event-based pattern recognition [34,35,38], object detection [36], visual object tracking [28,30], and video captioning [32,37].",
    "Specifically, Chen et al. [4].",
    "propose EFV++ for event stream recognition with dual-stream representation and quality-aware differentiated fusion.",
    "Wang et al. [39] build the Event-PAR dataset and an RWKV-based framework for RGB-Event pedestrian attribute recognition."
  ]
}